PROFESSOR: iPhone
cases that look

00:29:35.950 --> 00:29:40.160
like Game Boys that make
it not look like an iPhone.

00:29:40.160 --> 00:29:42.274
Is that dishonest?

00:29:42.274 --> 00:29:43.815
AUDIENCE: It might
be dishonest but I

00:29:43.815 --> 00:29:45.673
think it's still good design.

00:29:45.673 --> 00:29:46.964
PROFESSOR: What about up there?

00:29:46.964 --> 00:29:49.807
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:29:49.807 --> 00:29:50.890
PROFESSOR: Little outlets.

00:29:50.890 --> 00:29:53.922
You can't figure out how to get
this thing in til you turn it.

00:29:53.922 --> 00:29:54.630
Dishonest design.

00:29:54.630 --> 00:29:57.610
Who thinks that's
a dishonest design?

00:29:57.610 --> 00:30:00.530
Who thinks it's an
honest design anyway?

00:30:00.530 --> 00:30:01.147
Interesting.

00:30:01.147 --> 00:30:01.980
What about this one.

00:30:01.980 --> 00:30:05.930
What about childproof
bottle caps?

00:30:05.930 --> 00:30:08.010
It looks like they
could be opened,

00:30:08.010 --> 00:30:12.280
but if you are without the
skill, strength, or intellect,

00:30:12.280 --> 00:30:15.610
then you won't be
able to open this.

00:30:15.610 --> 00:30:18.450
Childproof bottle caps don't
just affect children though.

00:30:18.450 --> 00:30:20.210
They can affect adults who
simply don't have the strength

00:30:20.210 --> 00:30:22.960
to be able to open one of these
things-- to push down and open.

00:30:22.960 --> 00:30:25.810
So they have other designs
to get around that as well.

00:30:25.810 --> 00:30:28.105
But they're still a good design.

00:30:28.105 --> 00:30:30.370
But is that a bit dishonest?

00:30:30.370 --> 00:30:33.070
To give a whole population the
idea that it can be opened,

00:30:33.070 --> 00:30:35.050
but you can't open it?

00:30:35.050 --> 00:30:36.650
I'm not sure.

