PROFESSOR: Yes.

00:40:10.136 --> 00:40:11.440
AUDIENCE: Was he blindfolded?

00:40:11.440 --> 00:40:14.100
PROFESSOR: Yes.

00:40:14.100 --> 00:40:18.579
If you happen to know
this particular question.

00:40:18.579 --> 00:40:19.370
Was he blindfolded?

00:40:19.370 --> 00:40:19.920
Yes.

00:40:19.920 --> 00:40:22.160
AUDIENCE: Did he die
because the music stopped?

00:40:22.160 --> 00:40:24.160
PROFESSOR: Did he die
because the music stopped?

00:40:24.160 --> 00:40:25.778
No.

00:40:25.778 --> 00:40:29.974
AUDIENCE: Is this a human
man who actually died and was

00:40:29.974 --> 00:40:31.912
living and then now
is no longer living?

00:40:31.912 --> 00:40:34.120
PROFESSOR: Was it a human
man who died who was living

00:40:34.120 --> 00:40:35.120
and is no longer living.

00:40:35.120 --> 00:40:37.160
Yes.

00:40:37.160 --> 00:40:39.100
AUDIENCE: Did the music
give instructions?

00:40:39.100 --> 00:40:40.891
PROFESSOR: Did the
music give instructions?

00:40:40.891 --> 00:40:42.252
No.

00:40:42.252 --> 00:40:44.570
AUDIENCE: Did he die while
the music was playing?

00:40:44.570 --> 00:40:46.653
PROFESSOR: Did he die while
the music was playing?

00:40:46.653 --> 00:40:48.620
No.

00:40:48.620 --> 00:40:50.110
AUDIENCE: Where'd this happen?

00:40:50.110 --> 00:40:51.665
PROFESSOR: Where
did this happen?

00:40:51.665 --> 00:40:53.290
AUDIENCE MEMBER 1:
Yes or no questions.

00:40:55.914 --> 00:40:57.664
AUDIENCE MEMBER 2:
Does the music stopping

00:40:57.664 --> 00:41:01.080
coincide with the man's death?

00:41:01.080 --> 00:41:03.867
PROFESSOR: The music stopped and
coincided with the man's death.

00:41:03.867 --> 00:41:04.700
What's the question?

00:41:04.700 --> 00:41:08.892
AUDIENCE: Did the music
coincide with the man's death?

00:41:08.892 --> 00:41:10.850
PROFESSOR: I don't know
how to answer that one.

